Element.HELP: AFP multi doc RA payment Percentage
Element.DESCRIPTION:
AFP multi doc RA payment Percentage
After the RA is run file f075 is updated with doctor
payments. It is then determined what percentage each of the
doctor`s individual RMA doctor`s numbers contributed to the
total payments. This percentage for this RMA doctor number
is shown in this field.
The system will use this percentage to split the AFP payment
apportionately among the doctor`s RMA doctor numbers.
Note for if the doctor has only 1 RMA doctor number then
this percentage is alway 1.00 ie.100%)

AFP Payment Amount
The MOH AFP payment is made at the Doctor`s OHIP number
level but must be paid out to the doctor at their RMA
number level. The total AFP `submitted` amount is
stored in afp-submission-amt and then factored by the
doctor`s afp-multi-doc-ra-percentage to determine this RMA
doctor`s afp payment which is stored in this field.
AFP Payment Amount - Payroll `A` (22)
AFP Payment Amount - Payroll `B` (MP)

Element.HELP: AFP Conversion Total Governance Payment Amount
Element.DESCRIPTION:
AFP Conversion Total Governance Payment Amount
The MOH AFP payment is made at the Doctor`s OHIP number
level but must be paid out to the doctor at their RMA
number level. The total AFP `submitted` amount is
stored in afp-submission-amt and then factored by the
doctor`s afp-multi-doc-ra-percentage to determine this RMA
doctor`s afp payment which is stored in field
afp-payment-amt. The sum of all afp payments for
a doctor is then stored in this field.

AFP RA payment Percentage
After the RA is run file f075 is updated with doctor
payments. It is then determined what percentage each of the
doctor`s individual RMA doctor`s numbers contributed to the
total payments. This percentage for this RMA doctor number
is shown in this field.
The system will use this percentage to split the AFP payment
apportionately among the doctor`s RMA doctor numbers.
Note for if the doctor has only 1 RMA doctor number then
this percentage is alway 1.00 ie.100%)

Element.HEADING: Pay^Code
Element.LABEL: Pay Code
Element.DESCRIPTION:
Pay Code - valid values are `0` to `4` inclusive and `6`
0 - No Pay
1 - Ceiling payment - see also pay Subcode
2 - Paid what is Billed
3 - YTD Income - YTD Earnings
4 - YTD Income - YTD Earnings - YTD Expenses - see Subcode

The Pay SUBCODE is required for Pay Code 1 doctors.

`A` - is a DRAW on income. this is not guaranteed income
but rather is assistance with cash flow and must be
billings must eventually cover this amount.
`B` - is GUARANTEED Income to cover the short fall of
billings against the ceiling amount. this income
is guaranteed and therefore no billings are ever
required.
`C` - is used most often for sabbaticals or sick leave and
is a `TRUE` or `FULL` GUARANTEE. NO billings are
required. the guarantee doesn`t have to be fully
covered, eg sabbatical where only say 50% is covered.
In this partial coverage situation, if the doctor
is transferred to sub code D, the balance of the
can be earned if the income to date covers the
guarantee income in 1C.


The pay Sub Code is required for PAY CODE 2 doctors.

`A` - is the `normal` subcode for Pay Code 2. The doctor is
paid the full amount of their billings affected only
by the `factor` on their regular billing comp code.
`B` - indicates the doctor is not paid until they meet a
preset amount indicated by a deduction comp code. The
subcode is used to identify these doctors and to
do special processing - GST comp code is created and
descriptions of comp codes on pay statements are also
changed.


The pay Sub Code is required for PAY CODE 4 doctors.

R.A. Payment Amount
This is the total RMA payments from the last R.A. for this
particular RMA doctor number. It is compared against the
sum of RA payments (ra-payment-amt-total) for all of the
doctor`s RMA numbers to derive an individual RMA doctor
RA payment percentage which is stored in
afp-multi-doc-ra-percentage.

R.A. Total Payment Amount
This is the total RMA payments from the last R.A.for all of
a doctor`s RMA doctor numbers. It is compared against the
individual RMA doctor number RA payments (ra-payment-amt)
to derive an individual RMA doctor RA payment percenrage
which is stored in afp-multi-doc-ra-percentage
